SIMPLE: jointer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jointer
<hw>Joint"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, joints.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A plane for smoothing the surfaces of pieces which
are to be accurately joined</def>; <specif>especially:</specif>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The longest plane used by a joiner.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<fld>(Coopering)</fld> <def>A long stationary plane, for planing the
edges of barrel staves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Masonry)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A bent piece of
iron inserted to strengthen the joints of a wall.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A tool for pointing the joints in brickwork.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Joint-fir</ent>⟦br⟧
